profile_positions.description:
- Coordinating and overseeing the activity of the +40 members of the Committee working in 4 teams and task forces - namely, Erasmus+, European Universities, Global Mobility, Youth Engagement - and being the point of contact for the other 4 teams of the Education and Policy Department of ESN’s HQ in Brussels;
- Reporting to the President of ESN AISBL, lead the Chairing Team of the Committee. In charge of the overall coordination of the Committee and quality management of its outputs, In charge of projects and works directly with the coordinators to follow the progress of their projects;
- Internal and external representation of the International Committee for Education of ESN AISBL in the fields of expertise;
- Management of budget 
- Knowledge of ESN’s advocacy efforts and policy work in the fields of education and youth; Good knowledge of ESN’s programmes and projects related to research, mobility, and higher education; Good knowledge of the Erasmus+ programme; Good knowledge of decision-making processes within the European Institutions.

After creating the first Exchange Student online community, at 19 I joined YouAbroad as a Digital Marketing trainee. I grew and learned to then become the Social Media and Communication Coordinator, empowering the values of studying abroad towards prospective consumers and our internal community.

- Aligned with the CEO and Marketing Manager, designing and overseeing communications processes, marketing decisions and engagement strategies;
- Lead the social media and communication team and being a key account with internal teams  and external stakeholders;
- Founder and manager of the Social Media and Community team (21k followers on Instagram; 24k followers on TikTok); in charge of the overall recruitment communication strategy, from social media to the website, brochures, printed materials, gadgets and newsletters.
- Event recruitment strategy management, management of stakeholders, communication, sign-ups, logistics and event programs; national Info days, annual ya!Days event (up to +1000 sign-ups), online sessions, and pre-departure training orientation with up to 800 participants; 
- Managing the Ambassador Community  (+700 members) and enhancing the Storytellers Community (+800 students annually) by creating an online community, social events, merchandising and social media content. 
- Identifying trends and opportunities to amplify how stakeholders, influencers, and the education and travel industry are building community and bringing our mission to life
- Students and families support pre-enrollment to graduation;
- In-depth knowledge of Higher Education all over the world, working with national and international schools, with a focus on the United States, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, South Africa, UK and Ireland, and Nordic Countries;

volunteer_experiences.description:
The National Youth Council is in Italy the advisory body to which the representation of young people is delegated in the dialogue with the Italian institutions for any discussion on policies affecting the world of Youth. It was established with Law No. 145/2018.

Within its areas of competence:
- collaborates with public administrations by developing studies and preparing reports on the youth situation, useful for defining policies for young people;
- recognizes and promotes dialogue between youth institutions and organizations;
- promotes the active citizenship of young people supporting the activity of youth associations, enhancing the exchange of good practices and increasing networks. 

The Council participates with its representatives to initiatives at all levels, national and international, projecting the Council's action in an intercultural and intergenerational perspective.
